<plot>Everybody dreads laundry day, especially those of us who have to bang our socks on rocks in a river. But for those of us with modern creature comforts such as electric washers and dryers, we have become increasingly complacent over the ages with regards to this once awe inspiring ritualistic act of hygiene. And now we must pay the ultimate price for our apathy.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?321372</url></doc>
